<p>Yoast has 10 million active installs. Rank Math has 3 million and is growing fast. Picking between them is the most common SEO decision WordPress users face in 2026.</p>
<p>Most comparison articles bury the answer behind 4,000 words of feature lists. Here is the short version: Rank Math gives you more for free. Yoast gives you better readability analysis and a longer track record.</p>
<p>We have published 3,500+ blogs across 70+ industries on WordPress. We use both plugins daily. This Yoast vs Rank Math comparison is based on hands-on experience, not spec sheets.</p>
<p>Here is what you will learn:</p>
<ul>
<li>What each plugin offers in its free version (this is where the real gap is)</li>
<li>How pricing compares for single sites, agencies, and WooCommerce stores</li>
<li>Which plugin has better schema markup, speed, and AI features</li>
<li>When to choose Yoast, when to choose Rank Math, and when it does not matter</li>
</ul>
<h2>Quick Verdict</h2>
<p><strong>Best free WordPress SEO plugin:</strong> Rank Math. The free version includes redirect management, 16+ schema types, image SEO, unlimited focus keywords, and Google Search Console integration. Yoast locks most of these behind its $99/year premium plan.</p>
<p><strong>Best for content teams and readability:</strong> Yoast. The readability analysis (Flesch score, passive voice, transition words, inclusive language) has no equivalent in Rank Math.</p>
<p><strong>Best value for agencies:</strong> Rank Math Pro at $83.88/year covers unlimited personal sites. Yoast Premium at $99/year covers one site. For 10 client sites, that is $84 vs $990.</p>
<h2>What Is Yoast SEO?</h2>
<p>Yoast SEO launched in 2010 and has been the default WordPress SEO plugin for over 15 years. It holds 10+ million active installations on WordPress.org, with a 4.8/5 rating from 27,792 reviews.</p>
<p>Yoast introduced the green/orange/red traffic light system that taught millions of WordPress users the basics of <a href="/blog/on-page-seo-guide/">on-page SEO</a>. The Guardian, Microsoft, and Spotify use Yoast on their WordPress sites.</p>
<p>In 2021, Newfold Digital (parent company of Bluehost and HostGator) acquired Yoast. Since then, the plugin has added AI features, an AI+ subscription tier, and brand monitoring for AI search.</p>
<p><strong>Yoast is best for:</strong> Content teams that need readability coaching, enterprise sites that value institutional trust, and beginners who want a simple traffic-light scoring system.</p>
<h2>What Is Rank Math?</h2>
<p>Rank Math launched in November 2018 and now has 3+ million active installations. It grew roughly 300% since 2022 by offering most of Yoast Premium's features for free.</p>
<p>The plugin positions itself as a "Swiss army knife" for WordPress SEO. The free version includes redirect management, schema markup for 16+ content types, 404 monitoring, Google Search Console integration, and unlimited focus keywords per post.</p>
<p>Rank Math Pro ($83.88/year) adds a keyword rank tracker, advanced schema builder, and WooCommerce SEO tools for unlimited personal sites.</p>
<p><strong>Rank Math is best for:</strong> Site owners who want maximum features without paying, agencies managing multiple sites, and SEOs who want built-in analytics and rank tracking.</p>
