<h2>Migration: Switching Between Plugins</h2>
<p>Both plugins offer one-click migration tools. Rank Math imports Yoast settings, focus keywords, meta titles, meta descriptions, and redirects automatically.</p>
<p>Key considerations before switching:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Backup first.</strong> Always create a full site backup before deactivating any SEO plugin</li>
<li><strong>Meta data transfers cleanly.</strong> Titles, descriptions, and focus keywords import without issues</li>
<li><strong>Schema may need review.</strong> Custom schema configurations do not always translate perfectly</li>
<li><strong>Redirects import.</strong> Rank Math can import Yoast redirect rules during setup</li>
<li><strong>Rankings are not affected.</strong> Both plugins generate the same HTML output for search engines. Google does not care which plugin produces the meta tags. Your <a href="/blog/keyword-optimization-guide/">keyword rankings</a> will not change from switching alone</li>
</ul>
<p>The migration process takes under 5 minutes for most sites. Rank Math's setup wizard handles the import during initial configuration.</p>
