<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>Is Rank Math better than Yoast SEO?</strong></p>
<p>For most WordPress users, yes. Rank Math's free version includes features that Yoast locks behind its $99/year premium plan. The exception is content teams that rely on Yoast's readability analysis. That feature has no equivalent in Rank Math.</p>
<p><strong>Will I lose rankings if I switch from Yoast to Rank Math?</strong></p>
<p>No. Both plugins generate identical HTML output for search engines. Google does not know or care which plugin produces your meta tags. Rankings depend on content quality and backlinks, not which SEO plugin you use.</p>
<p><strong>Can I use Yoast and Rank Math at the same time?</strong></p>
<p>No. Running two SEO plugins simultaneously causes duplicate meta tags, conflicting schema markup, and XML sitemap conflicts. Use one or the other. Never both.</p>
<p><strong>Is the Rank Math free version good enough?</strong></p>
<p>For single-site owners, yes. The free version includes unlimited focus keywords, redirect management, 16+ schema types, image SEO, and Google Search Console integration. The Pro upgrade adds rank tracking and advanced schema, which are nice but not essential for most sites.</p>
<p><strong>Is Yoast Premium worth $99/year?</strong></p>
<p>Only if you specifically need Yoast's readability analysis combined with redirect management and multiple focus keywords. Rank Math offers comparable redirect management and unlimited focus keywords for free. The readability coaching is the only feature with no free alternative.</p>
<p><strong>Which plugin is better for WooCommerce?</strong></p>
<p>Rank Math. Basic product schema and WooCommerce support are free. Yoast requires a $178.80/year WooCommerce bundle. Rank Math Pro ($83.88/year) adds GTIN/MPN schema, WooCommerce sitemaps, and product page optimization for less than half the cost.</p>
<p>Pick the plugin that matches your actual needs. Rank Math if you want more for less. Yoast if you need readability coaching or AI brand monitoring. Either way, the plugin is not the bottleneck. Content is.</p>
